mercator
------------------------------------------
Mercator is primarily aimed at terrain for multiplayer online games and forms
one of the WorldForge core libraries. It is intended to be used as a terrain
library on the client, while a subset of features are useful on the server.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.4-1
  libgcc1-12.4.0-3
  libmercator0.3-devel-0.3.3-1bl4
  libmercator0.3_4-0.3.3-1bl4
  libstdc++6-12.4.0-3
  libwfmath1.0-devel-1.0.2-1bl4
  libwfmath1.0_1-1.0.2-1bl4
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  libtool-2.5.3-1
  libwfmath1.0-devel-1.0.2-1bl4
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/worldforge/mercator

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/worldforge/mercator/archive/refs/tags/0.3.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack mercator-0.3.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./mercator-0.3.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mercator-0.3.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/mercator-0.3.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmercator0.3_4-0.3.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmercator0.3-devel-0.3.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

